# Agent Startup Checklist MANDATORY

**EVERY agent session MUST start by executing the full startup checklist.**

## Startup Checklist Path
[docs/runbooks/agent_startup_checklist.md](mdc:docs/runbooks/agent_startup_checklist.md)

## Required Sections (Complete ALL Before Work)

**Section 0: Git Setup** (60 sec)
- Checkout `manager-reopen-20251020`
- Verify branch
- Review file ownership

**Section 1: MCP Tools Verification** (90 sec)
- Pull Context7 docs for libraries you'll touch
- Log tool usage in feedback
- Examples: Prisma, React Router 7, TypeScript, OpenAI SDK

**Section 2: Canon Review** (5 min)
- Read [RULES.md](mdc:docs/RULES.md)
- Read [NORTH_STAR.md](mdc:docs/NORTH_STAR.md)
- Read [OPERATING_MODEL.md](mdc:docs/OPERATING_MODEL.md)

**Section 3: Direction & Project Plan** (5 min)
- Read `docs/directions/{your-agent}.md`
- Read [PROJECT_PLAN.md](mdc:docs/manager/PROJECT_PLAN.md)

**Section 4: Tools & Environment** (5 min)
- Verify tooling
- Check credentials in `vault/occ/`

**Section 5: Work Protocol** (5 min)
- Database safety rules
- Evidence logging format
- Credential & blocker protocol

## Why This Matters

**Time Investment**: 20-30 min startup
**ROI**: Prevents 2-3 hours of P0 fixes per agent

**Real Examples** (2025-10-20):
- Skipping MCP tools → 13 failed deploys, 39 min wasted
- Using MCP tools → 3 deploys, 9 min total

## DO NOT
- ❌ Skip startup checklist
- ❌ Jump straight into coding
- ❌ Use training data without verifying with Context7
- ❌ Commit without checking file ownership
